					<h4>Procedure to register a product</h4>
					<p>Organizations that want to register a product in the DAPconstrucción<sup>®</sup> program must be affiliated and: 
					<ol>
					<li>Contact the Program Administrator (CAATEEB) to obtain the procedure for developing a DAPcons<sup>®</sup> and the Product Category Rules (RCP) applicable to your product. In the event that the CPR document for the product has not yet been developed, it will be necessary to start the procedure for its creation, or use the generic PCR, with the prior approval of the program administrator.</li>

					<li>Develop a Life Cycle Analysis (LCA) study in accordance with the corresponding Product Category Rules (RCP). The ACV report will follow the format determined by the RCP.</li>

					<li>Write a draft of the DAPcons<sup>®</sup> from the ACV study and following the guidelines of the procedure and the corresponding CPR.</li>

					<li>Carry out the verification of data through an accredited independent verifier.</li>

					<li>Once the verification is completed and if the result is positive, the organization must present to the Program Administrator (CAATEEB) all the necessary documentation and in accordance with the established models: DAPcons<sup>®</sup> verification report and report of ACV.</li>

					<li>Registration of the DAPcons<sup>®</sup> in the official registry of the Program, upon payment of the corresponding fee.</li>
					</ol>
